{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10673", "repo": "rails", "body": "Monkey-patching `BasicObject` does seem pretty serious. Its whole purpose is to have as few methods as possible.\r\n\r\n* Could you patch `Object` instead?\r\n* Even better, could you patch a few core classes like `String`?\r\n* Would a `respond_to?` check with a default case make sense?", "_id": {"$oid": "523cc514bd354364b90025ea"}, "issue_id": 10673, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/18152352", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10673#issuecomment-18152352", "updated_at": "2013-05-20T15:06:22Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris", "login": "jferris", "gravatar_id": "7fd56fa98da45bc532e898132085bd05", "html_url": "https://github.com/jferris", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/7fd56fa98da45bc532e898132085bd05?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F274231193c4e40abc64d2f2d8cb6b415.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 7591, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jferris/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-05-20T15:06:22Z", "id": 18152352, "owner": "rails"}
